02:07.649 --> 02:08.911
-MITCH: EVERY YEAR,
HUNDREDS OF HOPEFULS SHOW

02:09.041 --> 02:11.392
UP AT BAYWATCH FOR
LIFEGUARD TRY OUTS.

02:11.522 --> 02:13.916
ONLY THE TOP 15 MAKE
IT INTO ROOKIE SCHOOL.

02:14.046 --> 02:16.832
THE FASTEST, STRONGEST SWIMMERS
USUALLY GET THOSE SPOTS,

02:16.962 --> 02:20.662
BUT EVERY YEAR SOMEONE MAKES
IT ON SHEER WILL POWER,

02:20.792 --> 02:23.143
COURAGE AND DETERMINATION.

02:27.451 --> 02:30.019
-MY FULL NAME IS
LEYLANI MILOA MCKENZIE.

02:30.541 --> 02:32.326
MY MOTHER'S NATIVE HAWAIIAN.

02:32.456 --> 02:34.458
I WAS RAISED IN HONOLULU
SO I PRACTICALLY

02:34.589 --> 02:35.894
GREW UP IN THE WATER.

02:36.025 --> 02:38.201
I'M A CERTIFIED DIVER
AND I USED

02:38.332 --> 02:40.334
TO BE A FAIRY DECENT SURFER.

02:40.464 --> 02:41.944
-WHY DO I WANT THIS JOB?

02:42.118 --> 02:44.816
MOSTLY FOR THE BABES, I GUESS.

02:44.947 --> 02:47.558
NO, BUT I WORK REALLY
HARD AT IT TOO, YOU KNOW.

02:50.996 --> 02:52.737
-I'VE BEEN A LIFEGUARD
THE LAST THREE SUMMERS

02:52.868 --> 02:55.436
ON THIS LITTLE LAKE WHERE
MY FAMILY HAS A CABIN.

02:55.566 --> 02:56.785
IT'S IN WISCONSIN.

02:58.003 --> 03:00.180
-MY NAME IS CHERYL
WAYLIN AND I'VE ALWAYS

03:00.310 --> 03:03.139
LOOKED UP TO LIFEGUARDS EVER
SINCE I WAS A LITTLE KID.

03:03.270 --> 03:06.273
I'M GLAD I FINALLY HAVE
A CHANCE TO BE ONE.

03:09.014 --> 03:11.191
-I'M HERE BECAUSE
BEING A LIFEGUARD MEANS

03:11.321 --> 03:14.324
THAT YOU CAN MAKE A
DIFFERENCE IN PEOPLE'S LIVES.

03:14.455 --> 03:15.804
YOU KNOW, LIKE, SAVING SOMEONE

03:15.934 --> 03:17.893
FROM A DANGEROUS SITUATION.

03:18.023 --> 03:20.809
-I'M HOBIE BUCHANNON AND
I'M HERE BECAUSE MY DAD

03:20.939 --> 03:23.551
SAID IT WAS EITHER ROOKIE
SCHOOL OR SUMMER SCHOOL.

03:24.204 --> 03:26.989
-I WANNA BE A DANCER
AND A CHOREOGRAPHER.

03:27.119 --> 03:28.120
MAYBE SOME DAY.

03:28.251 --> 03:30.122
MY MOTHER WAS A
FAMOUS HULA DANCER

03:30.253 --> 03:33.387
BEFORE SHE MET MY DAD AND
STARTED HAVING BABIES.

03:33.517 --> 03:35.998
I HAVE FIVE BROTHERS
AND SISTERS.

03:45.050 --> 03:49.359
-MY FAMILY WAS ALWAYS INTO
BREAKING RACIAL STEREOTYPES.

03:49.490 --> 03:50.926
YOU KNOW HOW
THERE'S THIS THING

03:51.056 --> 03:53.233
THAT BLACK PEOPLE
CAN'T SWIM?

03:53.885 --> 03:56.714
WELL, MY MOTHER CHOSE
ME TO PERSONALLY PROVE

03:56.845 --> 03:58.020
THAT WASN'T TRUE.

04:03.460 --> 04:05.288
-ARE YOU COLD OR JUST NERVOUS?

04:05.419 --> 04:07.508
-A LITTLE BIT OF BOTH I THINK.

04:07.638 --> 04:09.727
I'M MOSTLY A POOL
SWIMMER, I'M NOT USED

04:09.858 --> 04:11.425
TO DEALING WITH THE ELEMENTS.

04:12.077 --> 04:13.992
-HERE, TAKE THIS, RUB
THIS ON YOUR ARMS AND LEGS.

04:14.123 --> 04:16.690
IT'S A NATURAL INSULATOR.
HELPS KEEP THE BODY HEAT IN.

04:17.168 --> 04:18.257
-THANKS.

04:18.822 --> 04:20.260
-HOLD STILL.

04:21.608 --> 04:23.306
-I WAS A STATE
CHAMPION IN HIGH SCHOOL.

04:23.437 --> 04:27.005
I STILL HOLD THE RECORD FOR THE
400 METER INDIVIDUAL MEDLEY.

04:28.485 --> 04:30.270
-OKAY, HERE'S YOUR NUMBER.

04:31.096 --> 04:32.750
-I'M CURRENTLY TRAINING
TO BECOME AN EMERGENCY

04:32.881 --> 04:34.012
MEDICAL TECHNICIAN.

04:35.057 --> 04:37.015
-ALL RIGHT, HOLD YOUR FIST UP.

04:45.110 --> 04:46.373
THANKS.

04:46.503 --> 04:48.505
-THIS YEAR, HOBIE
IS TRYING OUT.

04:48.636 --> 04:52.814
ONLY I DON'T KNOW IF HE'S
DOING IT FOR ME OR FOR HIMSELF.

04:59.211 --> 05:02.693
YOU LOOK TERRIFIC, HOW MUCH
SLEEP DID YOU GET LAST NIGHT?

05:02.824 --> 05:04.695
-ENOUGH.

05:06.436 --> 05:07.655
GIVE ME A BREAK ALL RIGHT?

05:07.785 --> 05:10.310
FRIDAY'S THE ONLY NIGHT
WE GET TO REHEARSE LATE.

05:12.137 --> 05:13.574
-DID YOU GET SOMETHING TO EAT?

05:13.704 --> 05:15.793
-YEAH, CONNOR'S
MOM MADE US OATMEAL.

05:15.924 --> 05:18.666
LOOK, DAD, I KNOW HOW
MUCH THIS MEANS TO YOU.

05:19.101 --> 05:20.842
I'M NOT GOING TO LET YOU DOWN.

05:23.801 --> 05:25.325
-MITCH: I REMEMBER
MY ROOKIE SUMMER.

05:25.455 --> 05:28.415
THE NERVOUS ENERGY,
THE ANTICIPATION,

05:28.545 --> 05:30.591
SOMETIMES I WISH
I COULD GO BACK

05:30.721 --> 05:32.723
AND DO IT ALL OVER AGAIN.

05:42.603 --> 05:44.082
-HEY, MANNY.

05:45.301 --> 05:46.302
-HEY, NEWMIE.

05:46.433 --> 05:47.782
-YOU READY FOR THE RACE?

05:47.912 --> 05:49.174
-WHAT ARE YOU KIDDING?

05:49.305 --> 05:51.612
I'VE BEEN HERE SINCE
THE CRACK OF DAWN.

05:51.742 --> 05:53.048
CHECK THIS OUT.

05:53.178 --> 05:55.616
-ALL RIGHT, NUMBER
ONE, YOU THE MAN.

05:55.746 --> 05:56.834
-I KNOW.

05:56.965 --> 05:58.445
-HEY, MANNY, SAVE A
LITTLE FOR THE SWIM.

05:58.836 --> 06:00.490
-NO PROBLEM.

06:00.621 --> 06:01.970
-COME ON.

06:04.929 --> 06:07.932
-CODY? CODY, REMEMBER ME?

06:08.063 --> 06:11.588
LANI MCKENZIE? I WAS YOUR DIVE
GUIDE IN HAWAII LAST YEAR.

06:12.197 --> 06:16.158
-YEAH, RIGHT. SO, YOU FINALLY
MADE IT TO THE MAIN LAND.

06:16.419 --> 06:18.073
YOU WANTED TO
BE A DANCER RIGHT?

06:18.203 --> 06:20.902
-YEAH, I REMEMBER YOU TALKING
ABOUT BEING A LIFEGUARD.

06:21.032 --> 06:22.469
FIGURED IT'D BE A GOOD
WAY TO SUPPORT MYSELF

06:22.599 --> 06:23.948
UNTIL I HIT THE BIG TIME.

06:24.079 --> 06:26.168
-WELL, GOOD LUCK TODAY.
-THANKS.

06:35.569 --> 06:36.874
-CHIEF: GOOD, OKAY.

06:37.005 --> 06:38.920
-CHIEF, YOU WANTED TO SEE ME?

06:39.050 --> 06:41.792
-YEAH, SO HOW DO
THE ROOKIES LOOK THIS YEAR?

06:41.923 --> 06:42.880
-[SIGHS] YOUNGER.

06:43.011 --> 06:44.882
-GET USED TO IT.

06:45.100 --> 06:46.318
-WHAT'S THIS?

06:46.449 --> 06:48.364
-THE RESULTS OF
THE CAPTAIN'S TEST.

06:48.495 --> 06:49.931
-HOW DID I DO?

06:50.061 --> 06:51.846
-WELL, IF I DIDN'T KNOW
ANY BETTER, I'D SAY SOMEONE

06:51.976 --> 06:54.022
SLIPPED YOU AN ADVANCED
COPY OF THE EXAM.

06:54.152 --> 06:57.417
-WELL, I PICKED UP A THING
OR TWO OVER THE LAST 25 YEARS.

06:57.547 --> 07:01.377
-MM, MY ONLY QUESTION
IS WHEN CAN YOU START?

07:01.508 --> 07:03.771
-[LAUGHS] JUST BECAUSE I
TOOK THE TEST DOESN'T MEAN

07:03.901 --> 07:05.425
I WANT THE JOB.

07:05.555 --> 07:07.296
-OH, COME ON, MITCH, YOU'RE
THE MOST QUALIFIED PERSON

07:07.427 --> 07:10.778
FOR THE POSITION AND I STILL
HOLD YOU PERSONALLY RESPONSIBLE

07:10.908 --> 07:11.909
FOR CREATING THE OPENING.

07:12.040 --> 07:13.520
-DON'T TRY AND PIN THAT ON ME.

07:13.650 --> 07:15.260
I WASN'T THE REASON
SAMANTHA QUIT.

07:15.391 --> 07:17.437
I JUST HELPED HER REALIZE
THAT MAYBE SHE WAS STILL

07:17.567 --> 07:18.873
IN LOVE WITH HER EX-HUSBAND.

07:19.308 --> 07:20.962
-FRANKLY, I NEVER UNDERSTOOD
HOW YOU TWO GOT TOGETHER

07:21.092 --> 07:22.354
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

07:22.485 --> 07:24.531
-COULD WE TALK ABOUT
THIS AFTER THE SWIM?

07:25.532 --> 07:27.011
-SURE.
-THANK YOU.

07:29.492 --> 07:33.191
ALL RIGHT, GOOD MORNING,
AND WELCOME. LISTEN UP.

07:34.236 --> 07:37.152
FIRST PRIORITY IS SAFETY.

07:37.282 --> 07:40.460
WHEN YOU RUN FROM THE
FINISH LINE INTO THE WATER,

07:40.590 --> 07:41.678
USE CAUTION.

07:42.200 --> 07:44.594
THERE ARE SEVERE IN SHORE HOLD.

07:46.117 --> 07:49.947
IF AT ANY TIME YOU FEEL
YOU CANNOT FINISH THE RACE,

07:50.687 --> 07:54.038
THERE WILL BE LIFEGUARDS
IN THE WATER TO ASSIST YOU.

07:54.517 --> 07:58.782
THE FIRST 20 FINISHERS WILL
BE GIVEN THESE RED STICKS.

07:59.522 --> 08:03.483
FROM THOSE 20, 15 WILL BE
CHOSEN FOR ROOKIE SCHOOL.

08:04.614 --> 08:05.702
GOOD LUCK.

08:06.268 --> 08:08.531
-I'M STUDYING FASHION
DESIGN AT CAL ARTS,

08:08.662 --> 08:12.100
SO I REALLY NEED THIS JOB SO
THAT I CAN STAY IN SCHOOL.

08:15.146 --> 08:17.932
-THE SWIM COACH AT
PEPPERDINE IS INTERESTED IN ME

08:18.062 --> 08:20.021
AS LONG AS I CAN
KEEP MY GRADES UP.

08:20.630 --> 08:23.459
-I ORIGINALLY WANTED TO WORK
IN AN ER, BUT THEN ONE DAY,

08:23.590 --> 08:25.156
I SAW YOUR CALL CAR
RESPOND TO AN ACCIDENT

08:25.287 --> 08:27.855
ON THE BIKE PATH AND I
REALIZED AS A LIFEGUARD,

08:27.985 --> 08:29.378
I'D HAVE THE BEST
OF BOTH WORLDS.

08:31.162 --> 08:33.904
-I'M GOOD IN THE WATER, I
LIKE COMING TO THE BEACH,

08:34.034 --> 08:35.645
I NEED THIS JOB.

08:37.559 --> 08:39.562
-EVERY MORNING AT
THE CRACK OF DAWN,

08:39.693 --> 08:42.522
SHE DROVE ME TO THE
MICHIGAN BAY SWIM CLUB.

08:43.000 --> 08:46.221
USUALLY AGAINST MY
WILL, BUT IT GOT ME

08:46.351 --> 08:49.311
A SCHOLARSHIP TO COLLEGE
AND HOPEFULLY THIS JOB.

08:50.399 --> 08:52.575
-YEAH, I NEVER REALLY
HAD A JOB BEFORE.

08:52.706 --> 08:54.838
OH, WAIT A SECOND, I
WAS A BOUNCER AT MY
COLLEGE FRAT HOUSE.

08:54.969 --> 08:56.318
DOES THAT COUNT FOR ANYTHING?

08:57.449 --> 08:59.364
-ASIDE FROM THE OBVIOUS
FAMILY CONNECTION,

08:59.495 --> 09:01.541
THE THING I LIKE MOST
ABOUT BEING A LIFEGUARD

09:01.671 --> 09:04.674
IS I CAN WORK DAYS AND HAVE
NIGHTS FREE FOR MY BAND.

09:04.805 --> 09:06.502
WE'RE REALLY STARTING
TO SOUND GOOD.

09:07.721 --> 09:09.287
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

09:09.418 --> 09:10.724
-JORDAN: SWIMMERS,
ON YOUR MARKS.

09:10.854 --> 09:11.638
-[GUNSHOT FIRING]

09:11.768 --> 09:16.294
-[SHOUTING]

09:46.847 --> 09:49.110
-THERE'S A REAL PROSPECT.

09:49.240 --> 09:51.503
LOOKS LIKE HER FEET ARE
STUCK TO THE BOTTOM.

09:52.330 --> 09:54.419
TEN BUCKS SAYS SHE DOESN'T
MAKE THE FINAL CUT.

09:54.550 --> 09:56.378
-YOU'RE ON.

10:19.357 --> 10:21.925
-COME ON, HOBIE,
STOP SCREWING AROUND.

10:29.106 --> 10:30.804
-NEWMIE: YOU'RE
GONNA OWE ME 10 BUCKS.

10:30.934 --> 10:32.762
-HOW DID SHE GET OUT THERE?

10:33.197 --> 10:35.852
-SHORT AND COMPACT
STROKE, NO WASTED MOTION.

10:36.548 --> 10:38.333
YOU SHOULD WATCH HER, YOU
MIGHT LEARN SOMETHING.

10:38.463 --> 10:41.336
-DOUBLE OR NOTHING SAYS SHE
DOESN'T MAKE THE FINAL CUT.

10:57.178 --> 10:59.267
-IT'S ABOUT TIME.

12:23.873 --> 12:25.570
-MAN: YOU'RE
ALMOST DONE! GO, GO!

12:47.592 --> 12:50.247
-[SHOUTING]

12:52.902 --> 12:54.599
-MITCH: COME
ON, YOU GUYS, GO!

12:54.730 --> 12:57.080
-[SHOUTING]

13:01.563 --> 13:03.391
-COME ON,
GO, GO, GO!

13:04.871 --> 13:05.785
-YEAH!

13:05.915 --> 13:07.482
