♪ SHAKE IT SHAKE IT

18:53.567 --> 18:55.134
♪ SHAKE IT SHAKE IT ♪

18:55.264 --> 18:58.354
♪ WHEN YOU SHAKE IT DOWN IT GET'S ME UP

18:58.485 --> 19:04.404
♪ SHAKE IT SHAKE IT [I NEVER LET ON]
I CAN NEVER GET ENOUGH ♪

19:04.534 --> 19:06.362
♪ SHAKE IT SHAKE IT

19:06.493 --> 19:09.887
♪ WHEN YOU SHAKE IT DOWN IT GET'S ME UP

19:10.018 --> 19:14.196
♪ SHAKE IT SHAKE IT
I CAN NEVER GET ENOUGH ♪

19:18.505 --> 19:21.986
-[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

19:29.429 --> 19:30.778
-DARREN?

19:30.908 --> 19:33.084
-I'VE ALMOST FORGOTTEN
HOW BEAUTIFUL YOU ARE.

19:33.215 --> 19:34.782
-LET GO.

19:36.044 --> 19:37.393
-SHE SAID LET GO.

19:37.524 --> 19:40.048
-DIDN'T TAKE YOU VERY
LONG TO FIND HIM, DID IT?

19:40.527 --> 19:41.397
-YOU KNOW THIS GUY?

19:41.528 --> 19:42.703
-YEAH, SHE KNOWS ME.

19:42.833 --> 19:44.052
NOW WHY DON'T YOU
LEAVE US ALONE?

19:44.183 --> 19:46.489
-NO, I DON'T THINK SHE
WANTS TO BE WITH YOU.

19:46.620 --> 19:48.665
-YOU KNOW, I DON'T REALLY
CARE WHAT YOU THINK.

19:49.013 --> 19:49.971
-OH, REALLY?

19:51.190 --> 19:52.452
-OKAY, PAL, GET OUT HERE.

19:52.582 --> 19:53.931
-THAT'S MY GIRLFRIEND.

19:54.062 --> 19:54.845
-NO, I'M NOT.

19:54.976 --> 19:55.846
-SEE YA.

19:55.977 --> 19:57.457
-BOUNCER: KEEP
MOVING, COME ON.

19:57.587 --> 19:58.501
-WHO IS HE?

19:58.632 --> 20:00.068
-YOU DON'T EVEN WANNA KNOW.

20:00.199 --> 20:01.896
-BOUNCER: GET OUT OF HERE.

20:02.026 --> 20:04.203
-[GROANING]

20:06.205 --> 20:07.771
-NOW I DO WANT TO KNOW.

20:08.337 --> 20:09.773
-DARREN AND I USED TO GO OUT.

20:10.209 --> 20:12.036
-WHAT WAS THAT BIT
ABOUT YOU FINDING ME?

20:12.167 --> 20:14.082
-I DON'T KNOW, HE'S CRAZY.

20:14.517 --> 20:16.302
HE THINKS I CAME TO
THE MAIN LAND FOR YOU.

20:16.432 --> 20:18.347
-WHAT? HOW IS THAT POSSIBLE?

20:18.478 --> 20:20.654
-WHEN YOU WERE DIVING IN
HAWAII, HE SAW US TALKING

20:20.784 --> 20:22.221
AND THOUGHT YOU WERE
TRYING TO HIT ON ME.

20:22.351 --> 20:23.222
-OH, JEEZ.

20:23.352 --> 20:25.093
LIKE I SAID, HE'S NUTS.

20:25.224 --> 20:26.573
-WHAT'S HE DOING HERE?

20:26.703 --> 20:29.924
-I HAVE NO IDEA. HE MUST
HAVE BEEN FOLLOWING ME.

20:37.801 --> 20:39.107
-HEY.
-HI.

20:39.238 --> 20:40.021
-WANT SOME COMPANY?

20:40.151 --> 20:41.370
-SURE.

20:41.501 --> 20:42.328
-YOUR NAME'S CHERYL, RIGHT?
-UH-HUH.

20:42.458 --> 20:43.720
-I'M LANI.
-HI.

20:43.851 --> 20:45.548
-HI. GOD, YOU'RE AN
INCREDIBLE SWIMMER

20:45.679 --> 20:48.203
-OH, THANKS, YOU, TOO.
-THANKS.

21:01.260 --> 21:04.306
-LANI. WE NEED TO TALK.

21:05.960 --> 21:06.874
ALONE.

21:07.353 --> 21:08.832
-IT'S OKAY.

21:10.138 --> 21:11.313
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

21:11.966 --> 21:13.968
-I PROMISED YOUR PARENTS
I'D CHECK UP ON YOU.

21:14.838 --> 21:16.362
-LANI: YOU TALKED
TO MY PARENTS?

21:16.492 --> 21:18.233
-MISS YOU
ALMOST AS MUCH AS I DO.

21:19.103 --> 21:20.975
THOUGHT MAYBE I COULD
GET YOU TO COME HOME.

21:22.281 --> 21:25.022
I CAME IN ON A FREIGHTER.
I'M LEAVING TOMORROW.

21:25.588 --> 21:26.720
I MISS YOU.

21:26.850 --> 21:28.548
I WANT YOU TO COME
BACK TO HAWAII WITH ME.

21:28.678 --> 21:30.854
-LOOK, DARREN, I
HAVE NO INTENTION

21:30.985 --> 21:33.770
OF GOING BACK TO HAWAII OR
GETTING BACK TOGETHER WITH YOU.

21:34.205 --> 21:36.860
I'M SORRY, BUT IT'S
TIME TO MOVE ON.

21:37.600 --> 21:39.298
HAVE A GOOD LIFE.

21:49.699 --> 21:55.052
-[SOFT MUSIC]

22:05.062 --> 22:06.760
-NEWMIE: ALL RIGHT, LET
ME HAVE YOUR ATTENTION.

22:07.282 --> 22:10.459
OKAY, NOW, IF YOU'RE
CAUGHT OUT IN HEAVY SURF

22:10.590 --> 22:13.636
WITH YOUR VICTIM, I'M GONNA
SHOW YOU GUYS WHAT TO DO.

22:14.376 --> 22:15.769
-WHAT'S GOING ON?

22:15.899 --> 22:18.772
-NEWMAN CAN'T WAIT FOR
ROOKIE SCHOOL TO START.

22:19.860 --> 22:21.601
BETTER GET IN THERE SO
YOU DON'T MISS ANYTHING.

22:21.731 --> 22:23.603
-HI! SEE YA.

22:23.733 --> 22:24.995
-LATER.

22:30.784 --> 22:35.397
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

22:35.919 --> 22:38.269
-NEWMIE: NOW, LET'S
GET STARTED.

22:38.400 --> 22:40.271
I NEED A VOLUNTEER. MANNY?

22:40.402 --> 22:41.316
COME HERE.

22:44.232 --> 22:48.105
ALL RIGHT, YOU REACH YOUR
ARMS AROUND THE VICTIM.

22:48.236 --> 22:51.674
YOU HOLD THE CAN TO HIS
CHEST, YOU LEAN BACK

22:51.805 --> 22:54.503
AND YOU FLOAT AND
YOU'LL STARVE TO DEATH

22:54.634 --> 22:55.765
BEFORE YOU DROWN.

22:56.462 --> 22:58.725
BUT REMEMBER, IF YOU CAN'T
GET IN, YOU WANNA STAY

22:58.855 --> 23:00.814
OUT BEYOND THE SURF LINE
AND WAIT FOR THE SCARAB

23:00.944 --> 23:03.251
OR ONE OF THE OTHER RESCUE
BOATS TO COME PICK YOU UP.

23:03.382 --> 23:06.297
YOU CAN'T AFFORD TO HARM
YOUR VICTIM OR PUT YOURSELF

23:06.428 --> 23:08.038
IN ANY KIND OF DANGER.

23:08.169 --> 23:10.127
IF YOU KNOW YOU'RE NOT
GOING TO MAKE IT IN,

23:10.258 --> 23:12.347
RAISE YOUR HAND UP REAL HIGH,
ONE OF THE BOAT LIEUTENANTS

23:12.478 --> 23:14.131
WILL SEE THAT YOU NEED
ASSISTANCE AND HE'LL GO AHEAD

23:14.262 --> 23:17.004
AND BACK THE BOAT BACK
INTO THE SURF LINE.

23:17.134 --> 23:18.962
ALWAYS APPROACH
FROM THE TRANCE.

23:19.093 --> 23:21.008
KEEPING AN EYE ON
THE BOAT LIEUTENANT.

23:21.138 --> 23:22.836
KEEP EYE CONTACT WITH
THEM ALL THE TIME

23:22.966 --> 23:24.968
BECAUSE IF AN OUTSIDE SET
COMES IN, HE'S GONNA HAVE

23:25.099 --> 23:26.840
TO HIT THE THROTTLE AND
GET OUT OF THERE QUICKLY.

23:26.970 --> 23:28.581
YOU DON'T WANT TO BE HALF
WAY GETTING THAT VICTIM

23:28.711 --> 23:30.974
ON BOARD THE BACK OF THAT
BOAT WHITE IT SETS [MUMBLES].

23:31.105 --> 23:32.498
THERE'S TWO
THINGS TO REMEMBER,

23:32.628 --> 23:34.761
ALWAYS KEEP EYE CONTACT
WITH THAT BOAT LIEUTENANT,

23:34.891 --> 23:36.719
ALWAYS MAKE SURE THAT
THE BOAT IS IN NEUTRAL

23:36.850 --> 23:38.417
BEFORE YOU ENTER THE AREA.

23:38.547 --> 23:40.810
-OH, MY GOD, WHAT'S GOING ON?

23:43.596 --> 23:44.640
-WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?

23:44.771 --> 23:46.033
-MY PROBLEM?

23:46.163 --> 23:47.730
MY PROBLEM IS THAT THE
WAVES AROUND HERE SUCK.

23:48.862 --> 23:50.211
-MAYBE YOU SHOULD
FIND ANOTHER BEACH.

23:50.341 --> 23:52.343
-MAYBE YOU SHOULD GET
YOUR ARMS OFF MY BOARD.

23:53.344 --> 23:55.608
-IF YOU'RE NOT GONE BY THE
TIME I GET BACK TO MY TOWER,

23:56.043 --> 23:57.305
I'M CALLING THE COPS.

23:57.436 --> 23:58.567
-WHAT DOES SHE SEE
IN A LOSER LIKE YOU?

23:58.698 --> 24:00.003
-START PADDLING.

24:00.134 --> 24:01.570
-WHY DON'T YOU MAKE
ME, BEACH BOY, HUH?

24:01.701 --> 24:03.442
I MEAN, COME ON, LANI'S
WATCHING, WHY DON'T YOU SHOW HER

24:03.572 --> 24:04.399
HOW TOUGH YOU ARE, HUH?

24:04.530 --> 24:06.488
COME ON, MAN, LET'S GO.

24:09.622 --> 24:11.101
COME ON, MAN, MAKE A MOVE.

24:18.021 --> 24:19.501
-NEWMIE: EVERYBODY STAY HERE.

24:21.721 --> 24:26.290
-[GROANING AND GRUNTING]

25:13.947 --> 25:16.558
HEY, LET HIM GO!
COME ON, LET'S GO!

25:18.865 --> 25:20.431
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?

25:21.345 --> 25:22.956
-THIS GUY'S A LUNATIC!

25:23.086 --> 25:24.479
-HEY, I'M OUT HERE SURFING
AND HE KNOCKS ME OFF MY BOARD.

25:24.610 --> 25:25.872
-NEWMAN'S THIS IS THE
GUY THAT'S BEEN FOLLOWING

25:26.002 --> 25:27.351
AND HARASSING LANI!

25:27.482 --> 25:28.527
-HEY, IF ANYONE'S GETTING
HARASSED, IT'S ME!

25:28.657 --> 25:29.528
I'M OUT OF HERE!

25:29.658 --> 25:31.138
-THE HELL YOU ARE!

25:31.878 --> 25:32.966
-NEWMIE: LET IT GO.

25:33.488 --> 25:34.358
-WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

25:34.489 --> 25:35.577
I'M HAVING HIM ARRESTED!

25:35.708 --> 25:37.405
-NO, YOU'RE NOT,
LET HIM GO, MAN.

25:37.536 --> 25:39.233
-WHY DON'T YOU COME
AND GET ME, BEACH BOY?

25:39.363 --> 25:42.062
YOU'RE LUCKY I DON'T COME BACK
HERE AND SUE YOUR ASS OFF.

25:43.542 --> 25:46.109
-COME ON, LET'S GO.
LET'S GO IN, COME ON.

25:49.330 --> 25:50.549
LET'S GO.

25:57.686 --> 25:59.906
WHO IS THIS GUY?
HOW DO YOU KNOW HIM?

26:00.471 --> 26:01.560
-[GRUNTING]

26:01.690 --> 26:03.257
WHERE DID HE COME FROM?

26:09.176 --> 26:11.570
-CODY, ARE YOU OKAY?
-YEAH.

26:13.006 --> 26:15.617
-YOU SHOULD BE CAREFUL.
THAT GUY'S A FREAK.

26:15.748 --> 26:17.097
-I DON'T KNOW WHAT'S
GOTTEN INTO HIM.

26:17.532 --> 26:19.578
I'M JUST SORRY THAT YOU
GOT CAUGHT IN THE MIDDLE.

26:20.100 --> 26:22.406
-DON'T WORRY ABOUT ME,
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

26:22.885 --> 26:24.713
-HE LEAVES FOR HAWAII TOMORROW.

26:25.192 --> 26:27.368
I'LL BE OKAY, HE'S
NOT GOING TO HURT ME.

26:29.892 --> 26:35.376
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

26:41.077 --> 26:42.775
-MITCH: HEY, HOB,
CAN YOU COME DOWN HERE?

26:42.905 --> 26:44.254
I NEED SOME HELP.

26:46.082 --> 26:48.041
-WHAT'S FOR
DINNER? I'M STARVED.

26:48.171 --> 26:51.435
-TACOS, WHY DON'T YOU START
WITH THE GUACAMOLE PLEASE.

26:54.221 --> 26:55.614
YOU KNOW, I WAS A LITTLE
SURPRISED YOU FINISHED

26:55.744 --> 26:57.833
SO FAR BACK THIS MORNING.

27:00.096 --> 27:01.663
-AT LEAST I MADE IT, RIGHT?

27:01.794 --> 27:04.318
IT'S NOT LIKE JUNIOR GUARDS,
I WAS UP AGAINST COLLEGE KIDS.

27:04.448 --> 27:06.407
-WELL, I THOUGHT YOU'D
BE MORE COMPETITIVE.

27:06.842 --> 27:08.148
YOU HARDLY BROKE A SWEAT.

27:08.670 --> 27:11.542
-ONCE AGAIN, I FAILED TO
LIVE UP TO YOUR STANDARDS.

27:11.673 --> 27:14.981
-ALL RIGHT, LOOK, WE HAVEN'T
REALLY TALKED ABOUT THIS,

27:15.111 --> 27:16.852
BUT IF YOUR HEART'S
NOT INTO IT, THEN MAYBE

27:16.983 --> 27:18.419
YOU SHOULDN'T BE OUT THERE.

27:18.549 --> 27:20.813
-DAD, JUST BECAUSE I DON'T
EAT, SLEEP AND BREATHE

27:20.943 --> 27:23.119
LIFEGUARDING DOESN'T
MEAN I'M NOT INTO IT.

27:23.772 --> 27:25.644
BESIDES, NO MATTER
HOW GOOD I DO,

27:25.774 --> 27:27.297
I'M STILL GONNA BE
COMPARED TO YOU.

27:27.950 --> 27:30.518
IT'S NOT EASY FOLLOWING IN THE
FOOTSTEPS OF A LIVING LEGEND.

27:30.649 --> 27:33.477
YOU MIGHT WANT TO TAKE
THAT INTO CONSIDERATION.

27:33.608 --> 27:34.827
-MAYBE I WILL.

27:34.957 --> 27:36.829
-THANK YOU.
-YOU'RE WELCOME.

27:37.699 --> 27:41.398
-SO, ANYWAY, WHAT DID THE, UH,
CHIEF SAY ABOUT YOUR PROMOTION?

27:41.529 --> 27:44.663
-WELL, WE HAD A LONG TALK
ABOUT IT THIS MORNING.

27:44.793 --> 27:46.012
-SO, WHEN'S IT
GONNA GO THROUGH?

27:46.142 --> 27:47.927
-IT'S NOT, I TURNED IT DOWN.

27:48.057 --> 27:49.929
-YOU'RE NOT GOING
TO BE CAPTAIN? WHY?

27:50.059 --> 27:52.583
-BECAUSE IT'S NOT WHAT I
WANT IN MY LIFE RIGHT NOW.

27:52.714 --> 27:55.021
-DAD, WHEN I SAY THAT ABOUT
COLLEGE, YOU GO BALLISTIC.

27:55.151 --> 27:57.371
-HOBSTER, I'M AT A POINT
IN MY LIFE WHERE I NEED

27:57.501 --> 27:59.286
TO FIGURE OUT
WHAT'S COMING NEXT.

27:59.416 --> 28:02.115
SO, I TOLD THE CHIEF, JUST
GIVE ME A TOWER SO I CAN WATCH

28:02.245 --> 28:04.944
MY WATER, I WANNA BE A NORMAL
EVERY DAY LIFEGUARD AGAIN.

28:05.684 --> 28:07.163
-AND WHAT'D SHE SAY?

28:07.816 --> 28:09.296
-THAT I NEED TO
SEE A THERAPIST.

28:10.079 --> 28:11.385
-MIGHT NOT BE A BAD IDEA.

28:11.515 --> 28:13.909
-THAT'S VERY FUNNY, HOW
MANY TACOS DO YOU WANT?

28:14.040 --> 28:15.302
-FOUR.
-OKAY FOUR.

28:15.432 --> 28:16.869
-LET'S GET SOME MORE
OF THESE AVOCADOS.

28:16.999 --> 28:19.698
-[SOFT MUSIC]

28:20.394 --> 28:21.874
-DONNA: THANK YOU FOR WAITING.

28:22.004 --> 28:23.832
I'M CONNECTING YOU TO
HIS TOWER, GO AHEAD.

28:24.528 --> 28:26.574
YOU KNOW, THEY DON'T TEACH
YOU THIS IN ROOKIE SCHOOL

28:26.705 --> 28:29.098
BUT THE SWITCHBOARD IS WHERE
MOST ROOKIES START OUT.

28:29.229 --> 28:32.362
-DONNA, THIS THING
BELONGS IN A MUSEUM.

28:32.493 --> 28:33.537
-[LAUGHING]

28:33.668 --> 28:35.496
-IT IS ANCIENT, BUT EFFECTIVE.

28:35.626 --> 28:37.716
OH, HERE WE GO, WHO
WANTS TO GO FIRST?

28:37.846 --> 28:39.195
-I'LL GO.

28:41.981 --> 28:43.460
-[BEEPING]

28:44.897 --> 28:46.855
GOOD AFTERNOON,
BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS.

28:46.986 --> 28:48.335
-[BEEPING]

28:50.511 --> 28:53.209
GOOD AFTERNOON,
BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS.

28:55.864 --> 28:57.083
THEY HUNG UP.

28:57.605 --> 28:59.433
-[BEEPING]

29:01.652 --> 29:03.872
GOOD AFTERNOON,
BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS.

29:04.003 --> 29:05.134
-YEAH, WHO'S THIS?

29:05.265 --> 29:06.092
-CHERYL: CHERYL WAYLIN.

29:06.222 --> 29:07.093
-HEY, CHERYL, IT'S CODY.

29:07.223 --> 29:08.485
-OH, HI, CODY.

29:08.616 --> 29:10.270
-OH, PUT HIM ON THE
SPEAKER. RIGHT HERE.

29:11.053 --> 29:12.707
-HI, CODY, IT'S
DONNA. WHAT'S UP?

29:12.838 --> 29:13.969
-CODY: HAVE YOU SEEN LANI?

29:14.100 --> 29:15.579
-NO, WHY?

29:15.710 --> 29:17.494
-SHE WAS SUPPOSED TO MEET
ME HERE OVER AN HOUR AGO

29:17.625 --> 29:19.453
AND SHE NEVER SHOWED UP.

29:19.583 --> 29:21.150
-CHERYL: I HAVEN'T
SEEN HER SINCE YESTERDAY

29:21.281 --> 29:22.761
WHEN YOU GOT INTO THAT FIGHT.

29:22.891 --> 29:25.589
-YEAH, HEY, BRO, WHAT WAS
UP WITH THAT GUY ANYWAY?

29:25.720 --> 29:27.504
-I DON'T KNOW, IT'S
HER OLD BOYFRIEND.

29:27.635 --> 29:30.029
-CHERYL: HE'S WEIRD, LANI
AND I WERE RUNNING ON THE BEACH

29:30.159 --> 29:32.553
THE OTHER DAY AND IT WAS
LIKE HE WAS STALKING HER.

29:32.683 --> 29:34.424
-I GOTTA FIND THIS GUY.

29:34.555 --> 29:36.165
DID LANI SAY ANYTHING
ABOUT WHERE HE WAS STAYING?

29:36.296 --> 29:39.299
-NO, BUT HE DID SAY HE'D
COME OVER ON A FREIGHTER.

29:39.429 --> 29:41.301
-FREIGHTER.

29:41.431 --> 29:42.955
DONNA, CAN YOU CONNECT ME
WITH THE HARBOR MASTER?

29:43.085 --> 29:44.434
-SURE, WHY?

29:44.565 --> 29:46.045
-CODY: I NEED THE NAMES
OF EVERY CARGO VESSEL

29:46.175 --> 29:47.960
THAT'S COME IN FROM
HAWAII IN, LET'S SAY,

29:48.090 --> 29:49.135
THE LAST WEEK.

29:49.265 --> 29:50.701
-YOU GOT IT, CODY.

29:51.964 --> 29:53.487
BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS
TO HARBOR MASTER.

29:53.617 --> 29:56.316
PATCHING YOU THROUGH TO
LIFEGUARD CODY MADISON.

29:56.446 --> 30:01.277
-[SOMBER MUSIC]

30:06.935 --> 30:08.284
-NOW IT WON'T DO
ANY GOOD TO SCREAM

30:08.415 --> 30:11.374
'CAUSE THERE'S
NOBODY ELSE ON BOARD.

30:11.984 --> 30:13.942
-DARREN, WHY ARE
YOU DOING THIS?

30:14.073 --> 30:15.639
DON'T YOU KNOW HOW
MUCH TROUBLE YOU'RE IN?

30:16.684 --> 30:19.295
-I'M JUST TAKING YOU
BACK WHERE YOU BELONG.

30:22.037 --> 30:25.301
-AGAINST MY WILL?
THAT'S KIDNAPPING.

30:29.392 --> 30:31.220
-LANI, I'M TAKING YOU HOME.

30:32.004 --> 30:33.962
NOW, SOMEDAY YOU'LL REALIZE
THAT WHAT I'M DOING HERE

30:34.441 --> 30:37.226
IS I'M SAVING YOUR LIFE.

30:48.585 --> 30:52.502
-[SOFT MUSIC]

30:59.945 --> 31:01.642
-SO HOW AM I
DOING SO FAR, DOC?

31:01.772 --> 31:03.209
-SO FAR, SO GOOD.

31:03.339 --> 31:05.515
-I'VE BEEN TAKING REALLY
GOOD CARE OF MYSELF.

31:05.646 --> 31:08.431
I'VE BEEN EATING RIGHT,
I'VE BEEN WORKING OUT.

31:09.215 --> 31:10.999
-OKAY, LOOK PAST MY SHOULDER.

31:11.782 --> 31:14.307
YOU NEED TO TAKE OUT
YOUR CONTACT LENSES.

31:15.525 --> 31:17.397
-I'M SORRY, I FORGOT
THAT THEY WERE IN.

31:17.527 --> 31:18.877
THESE ARE THE KINDS YOU
ONLY HAVE TO TAKE OUT

31:19.007 --> 31:20.356
LIKE ONCE A WEEK.

31:20.487 --> 31:21.314
-YOU WON'T BE ALLOWED
TO WEAR THEM DURING

31:21.444 --> 31:22.706
THE SIGHT TEST EITHER.

31:23.664 --> 31:25.144
STEP UP TO THE LINE.

31:29.409 --> 31:33.500
COVER YOUR LEFT EYE AND
READ EACH LINE SLOWLY.

31:34.109 --> 31:37.547
-E, F, P

31:38.070 --> 31:39.636
T, O, Z,

31:42.030 --> 31:44.772
E, B.

31:44.903 --> 31:47.253
-OKAY, COVER THE RIGHT EYE.

31:48.254 --> 31:49.908
START FROM THE SECOND LINE.

31:55.130 --> 31:58.786
-F, P, T, O, Z,

32:01.615 --> 32:06.185
E, B, O

32:07.099 --> 32:10.450
P, T.

32:31.688 --> 32:33.299
IS YOUR DAD STILL UP
THERE WITH THE DOCTOR?

32:33.429 --> 32:35.605
-HE JUST SPLIT,
LET'S GO TALK TO HIM.

32:36.911 --> 32:38.434
BRO, DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

32:38.565 --> 32:40.219
YOU DON'T HAVE TO HAVE 20/20
VISION TO BE A LIFEGUARD.

32:40.349 --> 32:42.525
-[EXHALES HEAVILY]

32:51.012 --> 32:52.448
DAD, IS IT COOL IF WE COME IN?

32:52.579 --> 32:53.667
-YEAH, YEAH, COME ON IN.

32:53.797 --> 32:56.583
LISTEN, CAN I CALL
YOU BACK? OKAY.

33:00.152 --> 33:01.849
-WHAT'S GOING ON HERE, MITCH?

33:02.502 --> 33:04.286
WHAT'D THE DOCTOR
SAY ABOUT ME?

33:06.767 --> 33:09.248
-MANNY, THE DOCTOR
SAID YOUR EYESIGHT

33:09.683 --> 33:12.294
DOESN'T MEET COUNTY
REQUIREMENTS.

33:13.817 --> 33:15.906
-HOW COME I HAD TO TAKE THE
TEST WITHOUT MY CONTACTS?

33:16.385 --> 33:18.300
I SEE A LOT OF VETERANS
AROUND HERE WEARING THEM.

33:18.431 --> 33:20.694
NEWMIE, CAROLINE?
WHY, MITCH?

33:20.824 --> 33:22.652
WHY IS THERE A DOUBLE
STANDARD FOR ROOKIES?

33:22.783 --> 33:25.916
-MANNY, CONTACT LENSES
AREN'T THE ISSUE HERE.

33:27.309 --> 33:29.050
IN ORDER TO BECOME
A COUNTY LIFEGUARD,

33:29.181 --> 33:34.316
YOU HAVE TO HAVE 20/30 VISION
WITHOUT CORRECTIVE LENSES.

33:35.361 --> 33:36.753
YOURS IS 20/40.

33:36.884 --> 33:39.104
MITCH, I CAN SEE JUST AS
GOOD AS ANYBODY OUT THERE.

33:39.234 --> 33:41.193
IN FACT, I NEVER HAD
A PROBLEM WHEN I WAS

33:41.323 --> 33:42.716
WITH THE JUNIOR LIFEGUARDS.

33:43.804 --> 33:46.589
I BET YOU DIDN'T EVEN
KNOW THAT I WORE CONTACTS.

33:46.720 --> 33:47.677
-I DIDN'T.

33:49.462 --> 33:51.594
-IS THERE ANY WAY
THAT I CAN APPEAL THIS?

33:53.509 --> 33:55.816
I CAN NEVER
BECOME A LIFEGUARD?

33:57.644 --> 33:58.775
-NO.

34:00.038 --> 34:02.736
NOT FOR THE COUNTY, NOT
UNDER THE CURRENT RULES.

34:03.171 --> 34:05.434
-WHAT ABOUT THE LASIK SURGERY
THAT GIVES YOU 20/20 VISION?

34:05.565 --> 34:07.349
I KNOW FRIENDS THAT
HAVE HAD IT DONE.

34:08.481 --> 34:10.351
-LIKE I CAN AFFORD THAT?

34:10.483 --> 34:12.050
GET REAL, MAN.

34:14.791 --> 34:17.272
-MANNY, THERE IS
ONE WAY YOU CAN STILL

34:17.402 --> 34:18.708
BECOME A LIFEGUARD.

34:20.101 --> 34:21.407
-HOW?

34:21.536 --> 34:23.148
-WELL, THEY'RE HIRING
AT THE SAND AND SEA.

34:23.277 --> 34:25.280
IT'S A PRIVATE CLUB AND THEIR
REQUIREMENTS AREN'T NEARLY

34:25.411 --> 34:27.195
AS STRICT AS THE COUNTY'S.

34:27.326 --> 34:29.806
THEY USUALLY TAKE THE
PEOPLE I RECOMMEND.

34:31.112 --> 34:35.333
-YEAH, SO THAT WAY I CAN
JUST BE DOWN THE BEACH, HUH?

34:36.813 --> 34:39.077
AND EVERYBODY WILL
KNOW I'M A REJECT!

34:39.686 --> 34:43.733
NO, THANKS, MITCH. I TRAINED
TO BE A COUNTY LIFEGUARD!

34:44.212 --> 34:46.606
NOT SOME SECOND
RATE CABANA BOY.

34:49.696 --> 34:52.002
WHO MAKES UP
THESE RULES ANYWAY?

34:53.482 --> 34:56.181
DID THEY KNOW THAT I WAS
AT THE TOP OF MY CLASS

34:56.311 --> 34:57.617
IN THE JUNIOR LIFEGUARDS?

34:57.747 --> 34:59.880
DID THEY SEE ME WIN
THE QUALIFYING SWIM?

35:00.010 --> 35:01.838
THEY DON'T KNOW JACK!

35:01.969 --> 35:03.927
BUT YOU, YOU DO, MITCH.

35:04.058 --> 35:06.800
AND ALL YOU CAN DO
IS THROW ME A BONE.

35:06.930 --> 35:08.845
THE BEACH CLUB?

35:10.673 --> 35:12.371
THANKS FOR NOTHING!

35:12.501 --> 35:15.896
-[GLASS SHATTERING]

35:22.685 --> 35:27.908
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

36:28.316 --> 36:29.361
-YOU REMEMBER WHEN
WE USED TO COOK

36:29.491 --> 36:31.189
ON THE BEACH AT KAPALUA?

36:33.930 --> 36:35.671
JUST YOU AND ME.

36:38.326 --> 36:40.502
TRADE WINDS BLOWING THROUGH.

36:41.286 --> 36:43.070
WAVES ROLLING IN.

36:49.337 --> 36:52.514
YOUR HAIR STILL SMELLS THE
SAME WAY IT DID BACK THAN.

36:56.431 --> 36:58.172
WHY ARE YOU CRYING?

36:59.956 --> 37:02.524
LOOK, NOBODY'S GONNA
HURT YOU, LANI.

37:03.264 --> 37:04.874
YOU TRUST ME, DON'T YOU?

37:06.049 --> 37:07.877
-YEAH, I TRUST YOU.

37:09.662 --> 37:11.838
I JUST DON'T LOVE
YOU ANY MORE.

37:14.623 --> 37:18.714
-[CREAKING]

37:19.889 --> 37:21.717
-BE A GOOD GIRL.

37:24.067 --> 37:25.808
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

38:08.198 --> 38:11.071
-[BANGING]

38:11.201 --> 38:13.552
-HELP! HELP!

39:15.962 --> 39:18.356
-YOU JUST COULDN'T MIND
YOUR OWN BUSINESS, COULD YOU?

39:21.054 --> 39:22.098
SHE'S MINE!

39:23.361 --> 39:28.801
-[SHOUTING]

39:39.159 --> 39:40.203
-ARE YOU OKAY?

39:40.334 --> 39:42.815
-I'LL SURVIVE, HOW ABOUT YOU?

39:42.945 --> 39:45.034
-LANI: IT'S BEEN A LONG DAY.

39:45.513 --> 39:47.080
-CODY: YOU CAN SAY THAT AGAIN.

39:52.694 --> 39:54.566
-NEWMIE: HOBIE'S
COMPETITIVE WITH YOU, MITCH.

39:54.696 --> 39:56.263
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

39:56.394 --> 39:58.483
-I THINK THE BEST THING TO
DO IS TO AVOID DIRECT CONTACT

39:58.613 --> 39:59.919
WITH HOBIE, YOU KNOW?

40:00.049 --> 40:01.834
I DON'T WANNA LOOK
LIKE I'M FAVORING HIM

40:01.964 --> 40:03.444
AND I DON'T WANT TO
BE OVERLY CRITICAL.

40:03.575 --> 40:05.098
I'M JUST GONNA LEAVE HIM
IN YOUR HANDS, ALL RIGHT?

40:05.228 --> 40:07.274
-WISE DECISION AS
OPPOSED TO YOU TURNING

40:07.405 --> 40:10.756
DOWN THE CAPTAIN'S JOB,
MITCH, WHAT ARE YOU THINKING?

40:11.234 --> 40:13.280
-NEWMIE, I WAS THINKING
ABOUT MY ROOKIE SUMMER.

40:13.411 --> 40:15.587
HOW I COULDN'T WAIT TO GET
TO THE BEACH EVERY DAY.

40:15.717 --> 40:17.502
YOU KNOW, I WANNA FEEL
THAT PASSION AGAIN.

40:18.285 --> 40:19.939
-YEAH, WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT,
I'D LIKE TO HAVE A FULL HEAD

40:20.069 --> 40:22.985
OF HAIR AGAIN BUT IT
AIN'T GONNA HAPPEN.

40:26.336 --> 40:28.295
-MANNY'S MOM CALLED
HEADQUARTERS AGAIN.

40:28.426 --> 40:31.646
SOUNDED PRETTY UPSET. SAID HE
DIDN'T COME HOME LAST NIGHT.

40:31.777 --> 40:33.082
-YEAH, YOU MIGHT WANT TO
TALK TO HER AND EXPLAIN

40:33.213 --> 40:34.344
TO HER WHAT HAPPENED.

40:35.041 --> 40:36.346
-WHY DON'T YOU GO AHEAD?
I'LL GET THINGS GOING.

40:36.477 --> 40:37.913
-ALL RIGHT, THANKS.

40:38.697 --> 40:43.789
-[SOFT MUSIC]

40:47.183 --> 40:49.185
-COME ON, MCKENZIE,
KEEP IT GOING.

40:52.711 --> 40:54.147
HEY, HEY, WHAT'S UP?

40:54.277 --> 40:55.975
-I'VE BEEN TRYING TO
EXPLAIN OUR OUTDATED VISION

40:56.105 --> 40:57.759
REQUIREMENTS TO MANNY'S MOM.

40:57.890 --> 41:01.502
ANYWAY, WHATEVER HAPPENED
WITH YOUR OLD BOYFRIEND?

41:01.633 --> 41:03.112
YOU GONNA BE OKAY?

41:03.243 --> 41:04.462
-YES, AS SOON AS HE
GETS OUT OF THE HOSPITAL,

41:04.592 --> 41:05.898
THEY'RE SENDING
HIM BACK TO HAWAII.

41:06.028 --> 41:07.552
-HE'S WANTED THERE
ON AN ASSAULT CHARGE,

41:07.682 --> 41:10.555
SO WE PROBABLY WON'T EVEN
HAVE TO TESTIFY AGAINST HIM.

41:10.685 --> 41:11.904
-YEAH, I JUST HOPE
THEY KEEP HIM AWAY

41:12.034 --> 41:13.775
FOR A NICE, LONG TIME.

41:13.906 --> 41:15.560
-WELL, NOW ALL I HAVE TO
WORRY ABOUT IS GETTING

41:15.690 --> 41:16.648
THROUGH ROOKIE SCHOOL.

41:17.300 --> 41:19.215
-WELL, IT LOOKS LIKE YOU
GOT A PRETTY GOOD COACH.

41:19.346 --> 41:21.827
-YEAH, WE'RE TRYING
TO KEEP HER IN SHAPE.

41:22.262 --> 41:24.482
COME ON, MCKENZIE,
STOP TRYING TO STALL.

41:24.612 --> 41:25.787
-ALL RIGHT. [LAUGHS]

41:25.918 --> 41:27.223
-MITCH: CATCH YOU GUYS LATER.

41:27.354 --> 41:28.703
-LATER-O!

41:30.836 --> 41:36.058
-[ELECTRIC GUITAR RIFF]

41:44.937 --> 41:51.073
-[END THEME PLAYS]
